        <h2>Networking Expert — Enterprise Networks &amp; Protocol Architecture</h2>

        <div class="two-col-text-img">
          <div>
            <p>Dr. Lavian is a networking expert and <a href="/">telecommunications expert witness</a> who provides consulting services in <a href="/communications-expert-witness/network-communications-expert-witness/">network communications</a>, telecommunications, and <a href="/communications-expert-witness/internet-expert-witness/">internet</a> protocols. He also serves as an <a href="/communications-expert-witness/internet-expert-witness/">internet expert witness</a>. His work covers network <a href="/us-10348313-radar-target-detection-system/">communications</a>, data communications, computer networks, and internet protocols, including TCP/IP, UDP, IP, MAC Ethernet, and IEEE 802.3.</p>

            <p>Dr. Lavian&rsquo;s academic background and practical industry experience cover the relationships between <a href="/us-20130080898-electronic-communications/">network communications</a>, computer networks, data communications, and <a href="/us-20180130102-reliable-rating-system-and-method-thereof/">wireless</a> applications. He has designed, implemented, and architected communications services in these fields.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <img loading="lazy" src="/images/heroes/network-communications-expert-full.svg" alt="Network Communications Expert"  width="360" height="240"/>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>Enterprise Networking Expertise</h3>

        <p>Dr. Lavian is a networking expert whose work covers network communications, computer networks, data communications, Internet protocols, and wireless applications, including their communication service architectures, designs, and implementations.</p>

        <p>His experience covers network communication routes, equipment architectures, and design, which are data communications components of the World Wide Web and Internet architecture.</p>

        <p>Dr. Lavian has worked with a wide range of networking and communications technologies, including:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Computer networks, network architectures, network protocols, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/pstn-voip-cellular-expert/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">communication systems, communication</a> devices, packet switching, networked systems, Internet technologies, distributed systems, and data center network architecture.</li>
          <li>Communication networks, Internet Protocols, <a href="https://wayback.archive-it.org/20635/20230207072736/https://www.ietfjournal.org/tcpip-25th-anniversary/">TCP/IP Suite</a>, TCP, UDP, IP, <a href="https://standards.ieee.org/featured/ieee-802/">Ethernet, 802.3</a> Internet protocols.</li>
          <li>Network software, data link, network, transport, and application layers (L2, L3, L4, L7).</li>
          <li><a href="/communications-expert-witness/network-security-expert/">Network security</a>, load balancing, Firewalls, IPSec, VPN, and Tunneling.</li>
          <li>Network protocols, Broadband, ICMP, IGMP, ARP, ARQ, HARQ.</li>
          <li>LAN, WAN, VPN, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/routing-switching-expert/">Routing</a> Protocols, RIP, BGP, MPLS, OSPF, Multicast, DNS, and DHCP.</li>
          <li>Bandwidth throttling, Quality of Service, QoS, Priority queuing, Classification, Provisioning, Packet Switching, and Switching.</li>
          <li>Quality of Service (QoS) relates to routing, switching, and communications systems.</li>
          <li>Network Communication Architectures, Network Infrastructure.</li>
          <li>Optical Networks, Optical Transport.</li>
          <li>Router, Switch, Bridge, Gateway, Edge Device, and core networking.</li>
          <li><a href="/communications-expert-witness/network-management-expert-witness/">Network Management</a>, MIB, SNMP, Edge Router, Core Router, Gateway.</li>
          <li>Internet Technology &amp; Infrastructure, Information Technology, Client/server applications, and 3-tiered architecture.</li>
          <li>Implementing such technologies over handsets, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/mobile-wireless-expert/">mobile devices, smartphones, cellular networks, wireless</a> technologies, architectures, standards, and systems.</li>
          <li>IP communications, digital communications, and network interfaces.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Background</h3>

        <div class="two-col-text-img">
          <div>
            <p>Dr. Lavian holds a Ph.D. in Computer Science from UC Berkeley, specializing in network communications, and spent nearly 20 years researching, studying, and lecturing at UC Berkeley&rsquo;s College of Engineering. He served as Principal Scientist and Principal Architect at Nortel Networks (1996&ndash;2007) and as a DARPA Principal Investigator.</p>

            <p>Dr. Lavian has over 120 <a href="/patents/">patents</a> spanning network communications, active network architectures, programmable forwarding engines, and <a href="/communications-expert-witness/data-communications-expert/">data communications</a> systems. He has over 25 <a href="/scientific-publications/">scientific publications</a> and has been retained in over 70 <a href="/cases-expert-witness-testimony/">cases</a>, including 80+ depositions, before U.S. federal courts, PTAB, ITC, and international tribunals, on behalf of over 50 law firms and corporate clients.</p>

            <p>His practical experience covers designing and implementing network architectures (LANs, WANs), configuring <a href="/communications-expert-witness/routing-switching-expert/">routers, switches</a>, firewalls, and gateways, and testing networks for performance, <a href="/us-10598764-radar-target-detection-and-imaging-system-for-autonomous-car/">security</a>, and interoperability.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <img loading="lazy" src="/images/content/media-streaming.jpg" alt="Media Streaming"  width="768" height="496"/>
          </div>
        </div>

        <section class="faq-section" aria-label="Frequently asked questions about networking expert witness services">
          <h2>Frequently Asked Questions: Networking Expert Witness</h2>

          <details open>
            <summary>What broad networking expertise does Dr. Lavian provide for patent litigation?</summary>
            <p>Dr. Lavian provides expert witness services across computer networking domains including LAN/WAN, wireless, Internet protocols, network security, VoIP, streaming, routing, switching, and network management in patent litigation and technical disputes.</p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Is Dr. Lavian qualified as a networking expert for both technical and litigation purposes?</summary>
            <p>Yes. Dr. Lavian combines 35+ years of hands-on networking industry experience (including at Nortel Networks), nearly 20 years of academic research at UC Berkeley, and extensive litigation experience as a testifying expert witness in 70+ patent cases.</p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What types of networking patent cases has Dr. Lavian handled?</summary>
            <p>Dr. Lavian has handled patent cases involving network protocols, router and switch architectures, network management systems, packet processing, VoIP implementations, network security mechanisms, and cloud networking technologies for major technology companies.</p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>How many networking-related patents has Dr. Lavian invented?</summary>
            <p>Dr. Lavian has invented 120+ issued and filed patents spanning network communications, telecommunications systems, active network architectures, programmable forwarding engines, network management, and data center infrastructure technologies.</p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Why hire a generalist networking expert vs. a specialist for patent cases?</summary>
            <p>Many patent cases span multiple networking domains &mdash; a VoIP patent may involve network security, routing, and QoS. Dr. Lavian&rsquo;s expertise across networking disciplines allows him to address cross-domain patent claims. His 120+ patents and Ph.D. from UC Berkeley span the full networking stack.</p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What companies has Dr. Lavian served as a networking expert witness for?</summary>
            <p>Dr. Lavian has been retained in networking patent cases involving companies including Google, Apple, Microsoft, Amazon, Intel, Cisco, Qualcomm, AT&amp;T, Verizon, Samsung, and many other major technology companies, providing analysis and testimony across the full range of networking technologies.</p>
          </details>
        </section>

